            "reviews": "“If you're looking for a fun and slightly different type of RPG that you can easily play in spurts, definitely give this one a go.”<br>95/100 – <a href=\"https://steamcommunity.com/linkfilter/?url=http://www.gamingnexus.com/Article/4421/Vertical-Drop-Heroes-HD/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"  >GamingNexus</a><br><br>“It is perfect for gamers who are into roguelike games and who also like platformers and RPGs. And of course, fans of Nerdook would certainly appreciate and enjoy this updated classic.”<br>8/10 – <a href=\"https://steamcommunity.com/linkfilter/?url=http://www.thatvideogameblog.com/2014/05/20/review-vertical-drop-heroes-hd-pc/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"  >ThatVideoGameBlog</a><br><br>“Dropping random heroes through strange 2D worlds until they meet their untimely, permanent deaths has never felt so exhilarating… Fun gameplay, lots of reasons to replay, great value!”<br>8/10 – <a href=\"https://steamcommunity.com/linkfilter/?url=http://www.gamesinasia.com/vertical-drop-heroes-hd-review-drop-it-like-its-hot/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"  >GamesInAsia</a><br>",
